# CHANGELOG: v8.1 → v9.0 (PHASE 0–3, BUILT FROM THE v8.1 AUDIT FINDINGS)

This version exists because a line-by-line audit of a *real generated page* (not this spec) found that the LLM doing the generating drifted from already-correct v8.1 rules under real conditions — most critically by inventing 11 wilaya names and copy-pasting one commune block across 13 different wilayas when `COMMUNES_DATA` wasn't actually supplied. v9.0 does not just repeat the rules louder — it removes the LLM's ability to be the source of truth for geography at all, and adds machine-checkable tests so drift gets caught instead of shipped.

| # | Problem found in the audit | Root cause | v9.0 fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Wilayas 59–69 fully fabricated/duplicated (11/11 wrong) | Model "filled the gap" from training memory because no real `COMMUNES_DATA` was injected for the test run | **Phase 0**: verified, citation-checked `WILAYAS_69` reference table now hardcoded *in this spec* (never generated) — see below |
| 2 | Wilayas 54 ("تيزي غانم" → should be "إن قزام") and 55 ("المغير" duplicated → should be "تقرت") also wrong | Same root cause, older batch | Same fix — full 1–69 table is now verified and frozen in this spec |
| 3 | Same 26-commune block copy-pasted across 13 wilayas (Oran, Tlemcen, Aïn Defla, Ghardaïa…) | No structural guard against the model padding missing data with a plausible-looking repeat | New **Rule 18** wording explicitly names this exact failure mode as forbidden, plus a standalone **commune-data validator script** (ships in `/tools`) that a human runs *before* any data ever reaches the LLM |
| 4 | `.qty-btn`/`.color-swatch` 34px, `.size-btn` 40px in the generated page, despite this spec's `.swatch`/`.pill` already specifying 44px | Spec compliance ≠ generation compliance — the model silently shrank targets under layout pressure | **Phase 1 Golden Test Suite**: automated tap-target scanner runs on the *output HTML*, not just trusts the prompt |
| 5 | Honeypot checked after submit-lock in the generated page, despite this spec already ordering it first | Same drift | Golden Test Suite checks the *compiled order of operations* in the output `<script>`, not just the spec |
| 6 | Emoji (🚚💵✅📞🧵📐🎨✨▶) used in live UI instead of inline SVG | Rule existed but had no enforcement teeth | Golden Test Suite emoji-in-button/icon scanner + Rule 53 self-audit step |
| 7 | Dead lightbox CSS/JS shipped for a Gallery section that was never rendered on that page | No rule required pruning unused section code | New **Rule 54**: any section/feature not generated must leave zero matching selectors/listeners in the output |
| 8 | No video support beyond a single hardcoded `./video.mp4` | Never speced | **Phase 2**: full Video Module (UGC vertical clips, hero autoplay/loop, captions, IntersectionObserver pause-offscreen, external hosting requirement for a multi-tenant pipeline) |
| 9 | Every regeneration repeats the same manual copy-paste of `COMMUNES_DATA`/brand data into the prompt, which is exactly how bug #1 happened | No separation between "rules that never change" and "data that changes per merchant" | **Phase 3**: Prompt Compiler architecture — static spec + per-merchant JSON + verified geo-data assembled programmatically, never by hand |
| 10 | Only one visual identity (editorial/Aesop-style) regardless of product or brand | No template selection existed | **Design Templates**: `DESIGN_TEMPLATE` selector with 4 distinct, fully-specified visual languages |

