# DESIGN TEMPLATES — MULTIPLE VISUAL LANGUAGES (NEW — v9.0)

v8.1 had one visual identity (the editorial/Aesop-style system specced above). Not every product or brand mood fits that — a Shein-style impulse dress and a Ramadan abaya drop don't want to look like the same boutique. `DESIGN_TEMPLATE` (set in USER INPUT SCHEMA) selects between four fully-specified directions. The Editorial & Animation systems above (typography, spacing, motion) stay shared infrastructure — what each template overrides is color, density, and a few section-level emphasis choices.

## 1. `editorial-aesop` (DEFAULT — this is the v8.0/8.1 system, unchanged)
- Calm, magazine-grade, generous whitespace, muted seasonal palettes (see `.theme-*` blocks above)
- Best for: premium abayas, structured pieces, brand-building first impressions
- Section density: relaxed — fewer competing CTAs per screen

## 2. `bold-shein-urgency`
- High-density grid, saturated primary color used aggressively (CTAs, badges, price tags), heavier use of the Inventory Pulse / countdown / "X يشاهدون الآن" social-proof features already in Conversion Engine v8
- Bundle pricing cards become the visual anchor of the page (moved higher, larger)
- Best for: impulse-priced items, flash drops, retargeting traffic that already knows the brand
- Still bound by Rule 43 (no fake urgency without real data) — "bold" is a density/color choice, not a license for dark patterns

## 3. `minimal-glossier`
- Near-monochrome (off-white/ink only), color appears *only* on the product itself (photos) and one accent micro-moment (e.g. the selected swatch ring)
- Larger type, fewer simultaneous animations (reveal + blur-up only — skip 3D tilt/magnetic buttons)
- Best for: skincare-adjacent framing, minimalist modest-wear, audiences sensitive to "salesy" pages

## 4. `heritage-ramadan-eid`
- Built on the existing `.theme-ramadan` / `.theme-eid` palettes but goes further structurally: lantern/geometric-pattern SVG motifs (inline, not emoji — Rule per Anti-Pattern Checklist) as section dividers instead of plain wave dividers, gold-foil-style CTA treatment
- Best for: seasonal campaigns specifically, not a year-round default even for Ramadan-adjacent product names
- Auto-pairs with `SEASON_THEME: "ramadan"` or `"eid"` but can be combined with other season themes for off-season "heritage" framing if explicitly requested

## Implementation note
`DESIGN_TEMPLATE` adds a `data-template="..."` attribute on `<html>` and a corresponding `.tpl-{name}` class scope; template-specific overrides live as additional CSS custom-property blocks layered on top of the base system (same pattern as `.theme-*`), not a parallel rewrite of the whole stylesheet. This keeps all four templates sharing one animation/JS engine and only diverging on the design tokens.

